                <h3>Enums</h3>
                <table class="guide-table">
                    <thead><tr><th>Enum</th><th>Values</th></tr></thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <tr><td><code class="code-inline">ReportStatus</code></td><td>Draft(0), Submitted(1), UnderReview(2), NeedsRevision(3), Validated(4)</td></tr>
                        <tr><td><code class="code-inline">CompletionLevel</code></td><td>Metadata(0), Partial(1), Full(2)</td></tr>
                        <tr><td><code class="code-inline">SnapshotType</code></td><td>Submission(0), Validation(1), PreEditBackup(2)</td></tr>
                        <tr><td><code class="code-inline">NoteType</code></td><td>General(0), CorrectionRequest(1), ValidationComment(2), RevisionReason(3)</td></tr>
                        <tr><td><code class="code-inline">ArtifactFileType</code></td><td>PDF(0), Excel(1)</td></tr>
                    </tbody>
                </table>

                <h3>Database Constraints</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><code class="code-inline">RosraReport</code> has a global query filter excluding <code class="code-inline">IsDeleted = true</code> records. Use <code class="code-inline">IgnoreQueryFilters()</code> to access deleted reports.</li>
                    <li><code class="code-inline">RosraReport.PublicId</code> has a unique index (GUID used in URLs).</li>
                    <li><code class="code-inline">ReviewNote</code> cascade-deletes with the parent report.</li>
                    <li><code class="code-inline">AnalysisSnapshot</code> uses restrict-delete to prevent accidental cascades.</li>
                    <li><code class="code-inline">ReportArtifact.SnapshotId</code> uses SetNull on delete.</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

